{\rtf1\ansi\deff0 {\fonttbl {\f0 Times New Roman;}}\f0\fs24 # Salem Coaching System - Privacy & Compliance Report\par \b Date\b : January 18, 2025  \par \b System\b : Salem University Coaching System  \par \b Prepared for\b : Regulatory Compliance Manager & Director of IT\par \par ---\par \par\b\fs28 EXECUTIVE SUMMARY / TL;DR\par \par\b\fs24 Current Privacy Protections\par - [OK]  \b No Persistent Storage\b : All student data processed in memory only\par - [OK]  \b Automatic PII Removal\b : Last names stripped before processing\par - [OK]  \b Encrypted Communications\b : TLS 1.2+ for all external connections\par - [OK]  \b Environment-Based Secrets\b : No hardcoded credentials\par \par\b\fs24 Compliance Status\par - [WARNING]  \b FERPA\b : Partial compliance - needs authentication & audit logging\par - [WARNING]  \b Title IV\b : Requires additional controls for federal aid discussions\par - [CRITICAL]  \b Authentication\b : Currently no access controls (critical gap)\par - [CRITICAL]  \b Audit Trail\b : No logging of who accesses student records\par \par\b\fs24 Immediate Actions Required\par 1. \b Deploy authentication system\b  (FERPA requirement)\par 2. \b Implement audit logging\b  (Title IV requirement)\par 3. \b Add consent mechanisms\b  (FERPA requirement)\par 4. \b Configure rate limiting\b  (Security best practice)\par \par\b\fs24 Risk Assessment\par - \b High Risk\b : Unauthorized access to student conversations\par - \b Medium Risk\b : Potential PII exposure in evaluation results\par - \b Low Risk\b : Data breach (no persistent storage)\par \par ---\par \par\b\fs28 DETAILED COMPLIANCE ANALYSIS\par \par\b\fs24 1. FERPA (Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act) Compliance\par \par #### 1.1 Current FERPA-Compliant Features\par \par \b Education Records Definition\b \par - System processes advisor-student transcripts containing:\par   - Academic performance discussions\par   - Career goals and plans\par   - Personal educational information\par   - Student identifiable information\par \par \b Data Minimization (34 CFR 99.31)\b \par ```typescript\par // Implemented: Automatic PII reduction\par const sanitizedTranscript = transcript\par   .replace(/\b([A-Z][a-z]+)\s+[A-Z][a-z]+\b/g, '$1 [LASTNAME_REMOVED]');\par ```\par \par \b No Persistent Storage\b \par - Transcripts exist only during processing\par - No database storage of student records\par - Memory cleared after evaluation completion\par \par #### 1.2 FERPA Compliance Gaps\par \par \b Authentication Required (34 CFR 99.31(a)(1))\b \par - \b Gap\b : No user authentication system\par - \b Risk\b : Unauthorized access to education records\par - \b Required Action\b : Implement role-based access control\par ```typescript\par // Needed implementation\par interface FERPACompliantAuth {\par   // School officials with legitimate educational interest\par   validateSchoolOfficial(user: User): boolean;\par   \par   // Audit legitimate educational interest\par   auditAccessJustification(user: User, record: string): void;\par }\par ```\par \par \b Consent Mechanisms (34 CFR 99.30)\b \par - \b Gap\b : No student consent workflow\par - \b Risk\b : Processing without proper authorization\par - \b Required Action\b : Pre-processing consent verification\par \par \b Audit Requirements (34 CFR 99.32)\b \par - \b Gap\b : No record of disclosures\par - \b Risk\b : Cannot demonstrate compliance\par - \b Required Action\b : Comprehensive audit logging\par ```typescript\par // Required audit log structure\par interface FERPAAuditLog {\par   timestamp: Date;\par   accessor: string;\par   studentRecord: string; // anonymized reference\par   purpose: 'evaluation' | 'coaching' | 'administrative';\par   authorization: 'school_official' | 'student_consent' | 'directory_info';\par }\par ```\par \par \b Directory Information Controls (34 CFR 99.37)\b \par - \b Gap\b : No mechanism to honor opt-outs\par - \b Risk\b : Disclosing opted-out information\par - \b Required Action\b : Directory information filtering\par \par #### 1.3 FERPA Implementation Roadmap\par \par \b Phase 1: Critical (0-30 days)\b \par 1. Deploy authentication system\par 2. Implement access logging\par 3. Add consent checkbox to UI\par 4. Create data retention policy\par \par \b Phase 2: Required (30-60 days)\b \par 1. Build audit report generation\par 2. Implement parent access portal\par 3. Add opt-out management\par 4. Create disclosure tracking\par \par\b\fs24 2. Title IV Compliance (Higher Education Act)\par \par #### 2.1 Title IV Considerations\par \par \b Federal Student Aid Information\b \par - Transcripts may contain:\par   - Financial aid eligibility discussions\par   - Satisfactory Academic Progress (SAP)\par   - Cost of attendance conversations\par   - Federal loan counseling\par \par \b Current Protections\b \par - PII sanitization reduces FSA ID exposure\par - No storage prevents long-term retention\par - Encrypted transmission to external APIs\par \par #### 2.2 Title IV Compliance Requirements\par \par \b Data Security (34 CFR 668.25)\b \par ```typescript\par // Required implementation\par class TitleIVCompliance {\par   // Protect Federal Student Aid data\par   sanitizeFSAData(transcript: string): string {\par     return transcript\par       .replace(/\b\d{10}\b/g, '[FSA_ID_REMOVED]')\par       .replace(/\b\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}\b/g, '[SSN_REMOVED]')\par       .replace(/EFC\s*[:=]\s*\$?\d+/gi, '[EFC_REMOVED]');\par   }\par   \par   // Track access to financial aid discussions\par   auditFinancialAidAccess(user: User, content: string): void {\par     if (this.containsFinancialAidData(content)) {\par       this.logTitleIVAccess(user, 'financial_aid_discussion');\par     }\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par \b Program Integrity (34 CFR 668.14)\b \par - Must prevent unauthorized disclosure\par - Requires systematic access controls\par - Needs regular compliance audits\par \par\b\fs24 3. Technical Privacy Implementation\par \par #### 3.1 Data Flow Architecture\par \par ```\par ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\par │   Student/       │     │  Load Balancer   │     │   WAF/DDoS      │\par │   Advisor        │────▶│  (HTTPS Only)    │────▶│   Protection    │\par └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └────────┬────────┘\par                                                            │\par                         ┌──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────┐\par                         │                                  ▼                  │\par                         │            ┌─────────────────────────────┐          │\par                         │            │   Authentication Layer      │          │\par                         │            │   - SAML/SSO Integration   │          │\par                         │            │   - MFA Enforcement         │          │\par                         │            └────────────┬────────────────┘          │\par                         │                         │                           │\par                         │            ┌────────────▼────────────────┐          │\par                         │            │   Authorization Layer       │          │\par                         │            │   - RBAC Implementation     │          │\par                         │            │   - FERPA Role Validation   │          │\par                         │            └────────────┬────────────────┘          │\par                         │                         │                           │\par                         │            ┌────────────▼────────────────┐          │\par                         │            │   Privacy Layer             │          │\par                         │            │   - PII Sanitization        │          │\par                         │            │   - Consent Verification    │          │\par                         │            │   - Data Minimization       │          │\par                         │            └────────────┬────────────────┘          │\par                         │                         │                           │\par                         │            ┌────────────▼────────────────┐          │\par                         │            │   Processing Engine         │          │\par                         │            │   - In-Memory Only          │          │\par                         │            │   - Encrypted AI Calls      │          │\par                         │            │   - Result Sanitization     │          │\par                         │            └────────────┬────────────────┘          │\par                         │                         │                           │\par                         │            ┌────────────▼────────────────┐          │\par                         │            │   Audit & Compliance        │          │\par                         │            │   - FERPA Logging           │          │\par                         │            │   - Title IV Tracking       │          │\par                         │            │   - Security Events         │          │\par                         │            └─────────────────────────────┘          │\par                         │                                                     │\par                         └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\par ```\par \par #### 3.2 Privacy Controls by Layer\par \par \b Layer 1: Network Security\b \par - Force TLS 1.3 minimum\par - Certificate pinning for API calls\par - DDoS protection\par - Geographic restrictions (US only)\par \par \b Layer 2: Authentication & Authorization\b \par ```typescript\par // FERPA-compliant access control\par interface AccessControl {\par   // Verify legitimate educational interest\par   hasLegitimateInterest(user: User, studentId: string): boolean {\par     return (\par       user.role === 'advisor' && user.assignedStudents.includes(studentId) ||\par       user.role === 'administrator' && user.permissions.includes('view_all_records') ||\par       user.role === 'compliance' && user.permissions.includes('audit_access')\par     );\par   }\par   \par   // Title IV specific access\par   canAccessFinancialAid(user: User): boolean {\par     return user.permissions.includes('financial_aid_authorized');\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par \b Layer 3: Data Sanitization\b \par ```typescript\par class PrivacySanitizer {\par   // Comprehensive PII removal\par   sanitize(text: string): string {\par     return text\par       // Names\par       .replace(/\b([A-Z][a-z]+)\s+[A-Z][a-z]+\b/g, '$1 [LASTNAME_REMOVED]')\par       // SSN\par       .replace(/\b\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}\b/g, '[SSN_REMOVED]')\par       // Student IDs (various formats)\par       .replace(/\b[A-Z]\d{8}\b/g, '[STUDENT_ID_REMOVED]')\par       .replace(/\b\d{7,9}\b/g, '[ID_REMOVED]')\par       // Emails\par       .replace(/[\w.-]+@[\w.-]+\.\w+/g, '[EMAIL_REMOVED]')\par       // Phone numbers\par       .replace(/\b\d{3}[-.]?\d{3}[-.]?\d{4}\b/g, '[PHONE_REMOVED]')\par       // Addresses\par       .replace(/\d+\s+[\w\s]+(?:street|st|avenue|ave|road|rd|lane|ln|drive|dr|court|ct|boulevard|blvd)/gi, '[ADDRESS_REMOVED]')\par       // Financial Aid\par       .replace(/\$\d+(?:,\d{3})*(?:\.\d{2})?/g, '[AMOUNT_REMOVED]')\par       .replace(/\bEFC\s*[:=]\s*\$?\d+/gi, '[EFC_REMOVED]')\par       .replace(/\bFAFSA\b/gi, '[FEDERAL_AID_REFERENCE]')\par       // Dates of birth\par       .replace(/\b(?:0[1-9]|1[0-2])[-/](?:0[1-9]|[12]\d|3[01])[-/](?:19|20)\d{2}\b/g, '[DOB_REMOVED]');\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par \b Layer 4: Audit Logging\b \par ```typescript\par class ComplianceAuditLogger {\par   // FERPA-required logging\par   logAccess(event: {\par     timestamp: Date;\par     userId: string;\par     userRole: string;\par     action: 'view' | 'process' | 'export';\par     recordType: 'transcript' | 'evaluation' | 'email';\par     justification: string;\par     ipAddress: string;\par     sessionId: string;\par   }): void {\par     // Write to immutable audit log\par     this.writeToAuditLog(event);\par     \par     // Alert on suspicious patterns\par     if (this.detectAnomalousAccess(event)) {\par       this.alertSecurityTeam(event);\par     }\par   }\par   \par   // Generate compliance reports\par   generateFERPAReport(dateRange: DateRange): FERPAComplianceReport {\par     return {\par       accessLogs: this.getAccessLogs(dateRange),\par       unauthorizedAttempts: this.getUnauthorizedAttempts(dateRange),\par       consentRecords: this.getConsentRecords(dateRange),\par       disclosures: this.getDisclosures(dateRange)\par     };\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par\b\fs24 4. Implementation Priority Matrix\par \par | Requirement | FERPA | Title IV | Priority | Timeline |\par |------------|--------|----------|----------|----------|\par | Authentication System | Required | Required | Critical | 0-14 days |\par | Audit Logging | Required | Required | Critical | 0-14 days |\par | Consent Management | Required | Best Practice | High | 14-30 days |\par | PII Sanitization Enhancement | Best Practice | Required | High | 14-30 days |\par | Role-Based Access Control | Required | Required | High | 14-30 days |\par | Disclosure Tracking | Required | Best Practice | Medium | 30-60 days |\par | Parent Access Portal | Required | N/A | Medium | 30-60 days |\par | Automated Compliance Reports | Best Practice | Best Practice | Low | 60-90 days |\par \par\b\fs24 5. Security & Privacy Controls\par \par #### 5.1 Current Security Measures\par \par \b Infrastructure Security\b \par - Environment variables for secrets\par - TLS encryption for external APIs\par - No database (reduces attack surface)\par - Serverless architecture (automatic patching)\par \par \b Application Security\b \par - Input validation (min 100 chars)\par - Output sanitization (removes AI preambles)\par - No file upload capability\par - Memory-only processing\par \par #### 5.2 Required Security Enhancements\par \par \b Access Control\b \par ```typescript\par // Multi-factor authentication\par class MFARequirement {\par   // Require MFA for all education record access\par   async validateAccess(user: User, request: Request): Promise<boolean> {\par     if (!user.mfaEnabled) {\par       throw new Error('MFA required for FERPA compliance');\par     }\par     \par     const mfaToken = request.headers.get('X-MFA-Token');\par     return this.verifyMFAToken(user, mfaToken);\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par \b Encryption\b \par ```typescript\par // End-to-end encryption for transcripts\par class TranscriptEncryption {\par   // Client-side encryption\par   encryptBeforeTransmit(transcript: string): EncryptedPayload {\par     const key = this.generateSessionKey();\par     return {\par       data: AES256_GCM.encrypt(transcript, key),\par       keyId: this.wrapKey(key),\par       algorithm: 'AES-256-GCM',\par       timestamp: Date.now()\par     };\par   }\par   \par   // Server-side decryption with audit\par   decryptWithAudit(payload: EncryptedPayload, user: User): string {\par     this.auditDecryption(user, payload.keyId);\par     const key = this.unwrapKey(payload.keyId);\par     return AES256_GCM.decrypt(payload.data, key);\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par \b Rate Limiting\b \par ```typescript\par // Prevent abuse and ensure availability\par class RateLimiter {\par   limits = {\par     unauthenticated: { requests: 5, window: '1h' },\par     authenticated: { requests: 100, window: '1h' },\par     api: { requests: 1000, window: '24h' }\par   };\par   \par   async checkLimit(user: User | null, type: 'web' | 'api'): Promise<void> {\par     const limit = user ? this.limits.authenticated : this.limits.unauthenticated;\par     const key = user ? `user:${user.id}` : `ip:${this.getClientIP()}`;\par     \par     if (await this.exceedsLimit(key, limit)) {\par       throw new Error('Rate limit exceeded - FERPA fair access requirement');\par     }\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par\b\fs24 6. Compliance Monitoring & Reporting\par \par #### 6.1 Automated Compliance Checks\par \par ```typescript\par class ComplianceMonitor {\par   // Daily automated checks\par   async runDailyCompliance(): Promise<ComplianceReport> {\par     return {\par       ferpaChecks: {\par         authenticationActive: await this.checkAuthSystem(),\par         auditLoggingActive: await this.checkAuditLogs(),\par         consentMechanismActive: await this.checkConsentSystem(),\par         unauthorizedAccessAttempts: await this.checkUnauthorizedAccess()\par       },\par       titleIVChecks: {\par         fsaDataProtection: await this.checkFSAProtection(),\par         financialDisclosures: await this.checkFinancialDisclosures()\par       },\par       securityChecks: {\par         encryptionActive: await this.checkEncryption(),\par         mfaEnforcement: await this.checkMFAUsage(),\par         rateLimitingActive: await this.checkRateLimits()\par       }\par     };\par   }\par }\par ```\par \par #### 6.2 Incident Response Plan\par \par \b FERPA Breach Response\b \par 1. \b Immediate\b  (0-1 hour)\par    - Disable affected accounts\par    - Preserve audit logs\par    - Notify security team\par \par 2. \b Short-term\b  (1-24 hours)\par    - Identify scope of breach\par    - Document affected records\par    - Prepare regulatory notification\par \par 3. \b Compliance\b  (24-72 hours)\par    - Notify affected students\par    - Report to Department of Education\par    - Implement remediation\par \par\b\fs24 7. Documentation & Training Requirements\par \par #### 7.1 Required Documentation\par - FERPA compliance procedures\par - Title IV data handling guide\par - Incident response playbook\par - Audit report templates\par - User access matrices\par \par #### 7.2 Training Programs\par - Annual FERPA training for all users\par - Title IV compliance for financial aid staff\par - Security awareness for IT staff\par - Incident response drills quarterly\par \par\b\fs24 8. Budget Considerations\par \par #### 8.1 Implementation Costs\par - Authentication system: $15,000-25,000\par - Audit logging infrastructure: $10,000-15,000\par - Security enhancements: $20,000-30,000\par - Compliance consulting: $10,000-15,000\par - \b Total estimated\b : $55,000-85,000\par \par #### 8.2 Ongoing Costs\par - Security monitoring: $2,000/month\par - Compliance audits: $10,000/year\par - Training programs: $5,000/year\par - Infrastructure: $1,000/month\par \par\b\fs24 9. Recommendations\par \par #### 9.1 Immediate Actions (Next 14 days)\par 1. \b Deploy basic authentication\b  - Even simple password protection is better than none\par 2. \b Enable audit logging\b  - Start capturing access patterns immediately\par 3. \b Add consent checkbox\b  - Simple UI addition for FERPA compliance\par 4. \b Implement rate limiting\b  - Prevent abuse while building full solution\par \par #### 9.2 30-Day Roadmap\par 1. \b Week 1-2\b : Authentication & basic audit logging\par 2. \b Week 3\b : Consent management & enhanced PII removal\par 3. \b Week 4\b : Compliance reporting & documentation\par \par #### 9.3 90-Day Goals\par 1. Full FERPA compliance certification\par 2. Title IV compliance validation\par 3. Security audit completion\par 4. Staff training completion\par \par\b\fs24 10. Compliance Certification Path\par \par To achieve full regulatory compliance:\par \par 1. \b Technical Implementation\b  (Days 1-30)\par    - Deploy all required controls\par    - Validate functionality\par    - Document procedures\par \par 2. \b Testing & Validation\b  (Days 31-60)\par    - Penetration testing\par    - Compliance audit\par    - Remediation of findings\par \par 3. \b Certification\b  (Days 61-90)\par    - External audit\par    - Regulatory filing\par    - Ongoing monitoring establishment\par \par ---\par \par\b\fs28 APPENDICES\par \par\b\fs24 Appendix A: FERPA Quick Reference\par - \b 34 CFR Part 99\b : Full FERPA regulations\par - \b Education Records\b : Any record directly related to a student\par - \b School Official\b : Individual with legitimate educational interest\par - \b Consent\b : Written permission from eligible student or parent\par \par\b\fs24 Appendix B: Title IV Quick Reference\par - \b 34 CFR Part 668\b : Title IV regulations\par - \b FSA Data\b : Federal Student Aid information requiring protection\par - \b Program Integrity\b : Requirements for data security and access control\par \par\b\fs24 Appendix C: Technical Standards\par - \b Encryption\b : AES-256-GCM minimum\par - \b TLS\b : Version 1.3 minimum\par - \b Password\b : NIST 800-63B compliant\par - \b MFA\b : TOTP or hardware token required\par \par\b\fs24 Appendix D: Contact Information\par - \b Compliance Questions\b : [Compliance Manager]\par - \b Technical Implementation\b : [IT Director]\par - \b Security Incidents\b : security@salemuniversity.edu (example)\par - \b Regulatory Notifications\b : compliance@salemuniversity.edu (example)\par \par ---\par \par \b Document Version\b : 1.0  \par \b Last Updated\b : January 18, 2025  \par \b Next Review\b : April 18, 2025  \par \b Classification\b : Internal Use Only}